<TITLE> Dialogue invite is a conspiracy: Rizvi </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 22 (bdnews24.com)BNP's acting office secretary Rizvi Ahmed said Tuesday that an invitation to the party's reformist leaders to dialogue by the Election Commission was a conspiracy. "It's part of a blueprint to isolate the BNP from elections," Rizvi, loyal to a faction led by Khandaker Delwar Hossain, told bdnews24.com in instant reaction to the EC's invitation letter. The EC has sent out a letter inviting BNP leader Hafizuddin Ahmed to dialogue for April 27, the chief election commissioner said. The dialogue has been scheduled for a 10am start. "The invitation letter will reach the address by tonight," CEC ATM Shamsul Huda had earlier told reporters, after a meeting with his colleagues at the EC. Rizvi has claimed that Delwar is the legitimate secretary general of the BNP. "Without him, a different leadership doesn't represent the party," he said. bd
